    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA124-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu pirivuṇarttappaṭṭa tōḻi talaivaṟku uraittatu (G1+2: talaivarkku uraittatu; ET: talaimakaṟku uraittatu).</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what the confidante who had been informed of the separation said to HIM.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA124">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            oṉṟil kālai yaṉṟil pōlap</l>
<l>            pulampukoṇ ṭuṟaiyum puṉkaṇ vāḻkkai</l>
<l>            yāṉumāṟ ṟēṉatu tāṉumvan taṉṟu</l>
<l>            nīṅkal vāḻiya raiya vīṅkai</l>
<l>            mukaivī yatiraṉ mōṭṭumaṇa lekkar </l>
<l>            navvi nōṉkuḷam paḻunteṉa veḷḷi</l>
<l>            yurukkuṟu koḷkalaṅ kaṭuppa viruppuṟat</l>
<l>            teṇṇīrk kumiḻi yiḻitarun</l>
<l>            taṇṇīr tataii niṉṟa poḻutē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>I cannot bear</l>
<l rend="indent2">the sorrowful life of staying in the grip of loneliness,</l>
<l rend="indent3">as the Aṉṟil bird at the time it is not one [with its mate],</l>
<l rend="indent4">and it has come by itself,</l>
<l>don't leave, may you live, lord,</l>
<l rend="indent2">– in the time that lasts<note place="foot">Can <term xml:lang="ta">niṉṟa</term> refer here to temporal extension: the time that has come to last? Another possibility might be to read it as an auxiliary of the continuous form in combination with <term xml:lang="ta">tataii</term>: the time when the cool water is permanently full.</note>, full of cool water,</l>
<l rend="indent2">when the clear water descends in bubbles,</l>
<l rend="indent4">to arouse longing, like a vessel taken to melt silver,</l>
<l rend="indent3">a depth(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">aḻunteṉa</term>: what the image might convey is the fact that the ground is momentarily flooded by water, thus suggesting a virtual lake (where the water would be deep). It could be understood as similar to constructions like <term xml:lang="ta">piṟaiyeṉa</term> nutal, only that here the noun for the ground walked by the deer is missing.</note> under the strong hoofs of the doe,</l>
<l rend="indent2">on the high sand dune with wild jasmine in blossoms</l>
<l rend="indent4">[and] the buds of mimosa.</l>
        </lg>
